...\" 
...\" .H 2 "Using the sec_admin Program"
...\" .P
...\" .iX "\*Lsec_admin\*O command" "description"
...\" While the DCE control program includes commands that create and maintain
...\" the master and slave replicas of the registry, the program does not
...\" provide functions that are useful for reconfiguring the replica set
...\" in a cell.  Reconfiguring the registry replica
...\" set in a cell involves reassigning the roles of the master and the
...\" slaves.  This reassignment of roles typically accompanies a change in the
...\" operations on one or more of the nodes in the cell.  It becomes desirable
...\" for some reason to change the site of the master replica, and the
...\" easiest way to move the master is to swap its role with a slave.  The
...\" \*Lsec_admin\*O program commands that you use to exchange master
...\" and slave replica roles are the \*Lbecome\*O command and \*Lchange_master\*O
...\" command.  The following subsections provide instructions for starting,
...\" stopping, and getting help on the registry editor, and provide brief
...\" descriptions of the \*Lbecome\*O and \*Lchange_master\*O commands.
...\" .H 3 "Starting, Stopping, and Getting Help"
...\" .P
...\" To start the \*Lsec_admin\*O program, enter the following command:
...\" .iS
...\" \*C$ \*Vdceshared\*L/bin/sec_admin\*O
...\" .iE
...\" .P
...\" Once invoked, \*Lsec_admin\*O enters the interactive mode in which you can
...\" execute commands.
...\" .P
...\" To exit from \*Lsec_admin\*O, enter the following command:
...\" .iS
...\" \*Csec_admin> \*Lquit\*O
...\" .iE
...\" .P
...\" To display a list of the \*Lsec_admin\*O commands,
...\" enter the following command: 
...\" .iS
...\" \*Csec_admin> \*Lhelp\*O
...\" .iE
...\" .H 3 "sec_admin Commands for Reconfiguring Replica Sets"
...\" .P
...\" .iX "\*Lsec_admin\*O command" "for reconfiguring replica sets"
...\" Table 29-3 provides brief descriptions of the \*Lsec_admin\*O commands
...\" for reconfiguring the registry's replica set.  Instructions for
...\" changing master and slave replica roles can be found in Chapter 40 of
...\" this guide.
...\" .TB "sec_admin Commands for Reconfiguring Replica Sets"
...\" .P
...\" .TS
...\" center,allbox,tab(@);
...\" lB | lB
...\" lb | lw(3.75i).
...\" Name@Description
...\" _
...\" .TH
...\" \*Lb\*O[\*Lecome_master\*O]@T{
...\" Causes a slave replica to assume the role of the master.
...\" T}
...\" \*Lc\*O[\*Lhange_master\*O]@T{
...\" Causes the current master replica to give its role to a slave and to become
...\" a slave.
...\" T}
...\" .TE  
...\" .P
...\" For detailed descriptions of the \*Lsec_admin\*O commands, refer to the
...\" \*Lsec_admin(8sec)\*O reference page.
...\" 
.zZ "def, 13575,R1.2.2,Removed sec_admin info"
